# {{PROJECT_NAME}} — Claude Code Instructions

Global, project-agnostic engineering principles come from this Agent OS
installation's `GLOBAL_AGENTS.md` and `GLOBAL_CLAUDE.md`. They apply here
and are not restated. Read them first if you have not already.

## Where things live

- **This file (CLAUDE.md)** — short, always-loaded pointers only.
- **`.claude/skills/*/SKILL.md`** — on-demand, long-form procedures.
- **`.claude/agents/*.md`** — specialized subagents (e.g. code reviewer,
  bug investigator) for bounded, scoped work.

## Project facts

- Read `.agent-os/project-profile.md` for observed facts: stack, structure,
  conventions, known risk areas.
- Read `.agent-os/command-map.md` for verified commands. Never invent one.

## Active learned rules

- Read `.agent-os/learned-rules.md` before making changes.
- Honor every rule whose `Status:` is `active`. `Status: candidate` rules
  are observations, not yet binding.
- If corrected during this session, record it in
  `.agent-os/review-feedback-log.md` (2+ occurrences promotes to active).

## Safety (non-negotiable)

- No destructive operations (`rm -rf`, force-push, dropping data,
  migrations) without explicit user approval.
- Never read, print, log, or commit secrets: `.env` files, keys, tokens,
  credentials.
- Only run verification commands confirmed in `.agent-os/command-map.md`.
- Never mark work done while tests, types, or lint are failing or skipped.

## When something fails

- Log it in `.agent-os/failure-log.md` with the exact command and error.
